# Architecture

## Layers (inner → outer)

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| Model | `model/` | Board grid, `Piece`, `Position`, `GameState` — data only, no I/O |
| Rules | `rules/` | `IPieceRules` strategies, `RuleEngine` move validation |
| Realtime | `realtime/` | `Motion`, `RealTimeArbiter` — timed movement and capture resolution |
| Engine | `engine/` | `GameEngine` — orchestrates model + rules + realtime; no I/O |
| I/O | `io/` | `BoardParser`, `BoardPrinter` — parse/serialize board text |
| Input | `input/` | `Controller`, `BoardMapper` — map user events to engine calls |
| Graphics | `graphics/` | `Animation`, `AnimationCache` (`AnimationSpec`), `AnimationLoader`, `BoardLayout`, `PieceVisual` — load/scale sprite frames, play named state animations, read asset board layout; depends on `Img` only |
| View | `view/` | `Img` (OpenCV wrapper) + `Renderer` — composites sprites, optional White/Black history HUD, drives the window; never mutates `Board` |
| Text tests | `texttests/` | `ScriptParser`, `ScriptRunner` — scripted stdin integration |
| Bus | `bus/` | `EventBus` Observer pub/sub — score/log/sound/UI/rating events (`MoveMade`, `JumpMade`, `PieceCaptured`, `PiecePromoted`, `PieceSelected`, `SelectionCleared`, `GameEnded`, `ScoreUpdated`, …); `MoveHistorySubscriber` stores graphics side-panel lines + SCORE; `RatingSubscriber` updates ELO on `GameEnded`; `capturePoints()` for material; logic does not know subscribers |
| Protocol | `protocol/` | Algebraic ↔ `Position`; plain-text commands in (`AUTH`, moves); JSON state/events out |
| Auth | `auth/` | `AuthController` → `UserService` → `UserRepository` (SQLite); `PasswordHasher` (bcrypt), `Elo` — server-only |
| Server | `server/` | `GameSession` + `WebSocketServer` — AUTH then network host, auto-tick, W/B seats |
| App | `App`, `GraphicsApplication`, `main`, `graphics_main`, `server_main` | Composition roots: console, graphics, WebSocket server |

## Dependency rule

Dependencies point **inward only**. Outer layers may use inner; inner layers must never include `view/`, `input/`, `io/`, `server/`, or `main`.

```
main/App → input/view/io → engine → rules/realtime → model
server_main → server/protocol/bus/auth → engine → rules/realtime → model
```

The graphics stack sits on the view side and depends inward on `view/Img` only:

```
graphics_main → GraphicsApplication → engine/input + graphics(PieceVisual) + view(Renderer/Img) + bus(MoveHistory/Sound)
GraphicsApplication → graphics/ → view(Img)
```

`GraphicsApplication` builds a wider window (`White panel | board | Black panel`) via `Img::create`, offsets `BoardMapper` to the board rect, and feeds `Renderer::HistoryHud` each frame (move lines + SCORE). On capture it publishes `ScoreUpdated` using `capturePoints()`. `GameEvent::timeMs` is stamped from `GameEngine::elapsedMs()` in graphics only (not the server path).

`graphics/` and `Renderer` must never `#include <opencv2/...>`; all pixel work goes through the `Img` API.

Server reuses the same `GameEngine` (no forked logic). `GameSession` publishes Bus events after engine calls; the network layer never embeds rules. `WebSocketServer` requires `AUTH` (via `AuthController` → `UserService`) before seating; `RatingSubscriber` listens for `GameEnded` and updates ratings via `UserService`.

## Design patterns

- **Strategy**: one `IPieceRules` per piece type; `RuleEngine` maps piece kind → strategy via `unordered_map<char, unique_ptr<IPieceRules>>`
- **DTO**: cross-boundary structs (`MoveResult`, `MoveValidation`, `GameSnapshot`, `ArrivalEvent`, `MotionView`, `RestView`) — plain data, no behavior
- **Facade**: `GameEngine` is the single entry point for game logic; `GameSession` is the server-side facade over it
- **Observer**: `EventBus` for MoveMade / PieceCaptured / GameEnded / ScoreUpdated / …
- **Snapshot**: view reads `GameSnapshot`; never mutates `Board` directly

## Adding features

1. Place logic in the correct layer — not in `main`
2. Expose results via small structs, not raw internal state
3. Keep abstractions generic: prefer interfaces + factories / `std::unordered_map` lookups over `switch` on piece kind (or other extensible keys). Examples: `RuleEngine` kind→rules, `capturePoints` kind→score, piece display names, sound cues. Reserve `switch` for small closed enum→string helpers only.
4. Validate at boundaries; assume nothing about caller intent inside engine

## Exception flow

Exceptions cross layers **upward only**; recovery happens at outer boundaries:

```
model / realtime  →  throw
rules / engine    →  catch → MoveValidation / MoveResult
input             →  catch → ClickResult / MoveResult
texttests / main  →  catch → log + ERROR RUNTIME_FAILURE or exit code
```

Inner layers never `#include <iostream>` for error logging. See `agents.mdc` for the full policy.
